\ph[90%]{../tobago/8041_2210_1.jpg}{
Auction: 8041 - Trinidad & Tobago 
Lot: 2210 TOBAGO Early Letters and Handstamps 1842 (19 Aug.) entire letter addressed to James MacQueen, founder of the Royal Mail Steam Packet Company, in London, rated "1/-" and showing, on reverse across join, Tobago double-arc d.s. with arrival d.s. (6.10) alongside. The historical contents include "It is truly astonishing to think of the way in which your Steam concern has been conducted and the total loss it would seem the Shareholders are doomed to suffer. It is astonishing that those of them upon the spot have not interfered before now. The loss will bear particularly hard upon me and the like of me but it cannot be helped" Photo Estimate £ 800-1,000 Note: The first nine operating months of the Royal Mail Steam Packet Company had been a disaster, and the Admiralty were keen that the R.M.S.P.Co. should not perform satisfactorily. With the assistance of the Royal Navy, the Admiralty revised operations and thus saved the company from collapse. provenance: Ben Ramkissoon, 2006 Sold for £650
}

